---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import HeroBanner from '../components/HeroBanner.astro';
import ResourceCard from '../components/ResourceCard.astro';
import InfoSection from '../components/InfoSection.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Get Help Now | MindSpace"
  description="Immediate resources and support for teens experiencing mental health crises or needing professional help."
>
  <Header slot="header" />
  
  <HeroBanner 
    title="Need Support? You're Not Alone."
    subtitle="Whether you're in crisis or just need someone to talk to, help is available right now. Your mental health matters."
    ctaText="Crisis Resources"
    ctaLink="#crisis"
    secondaryCtaText="Talk to Someone"
    secondaryCtaLink="#talk"
    imageSrc="https://images.pexels.com/photos/4101142/pexels-photo-4101142.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
  />
  
  <!-- Immediate Crisis Resources -->
  <section id="crisis" class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <div class="inline-block p-2 bg-red-50 rounded-lg mb-4 animate-on-scroll">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-red-600" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4m0 4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-4 animate-on-scroll">Immediate Crisis Support</h2>
        <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-neutral-600 animate-on-scroll">
          If you're experiencing a mental health emergency or having thoughts of suicide, 
          please use these resources to get immediate help.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-red-100 animate-on-scroll">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-4">Suicide & Crisis Lifeline</h3>
          <div class="text-center py-4 bg-white rounded-lg mb-4">
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold">988</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Call or Text 24/7</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">The 988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline provides free and confidential emotional support to people in suicidal crisis or emotional distress 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.</p>
          <a 
            href="https://988lifeline.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full px-4 py-2 bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Visit Website
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 ml-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-red-100 animate-on-scroll">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-4">Crisis Text Line</h3>
          <div class="text-center py-4 bg-white rounded-lg mb-4">
            <p class="text-xl font-bold">Text HOME to 741741</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Free, 24/7 Crisis Counseling</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Crisis Text Line serves anyone, in any type of crisis, providing access to free, 24/7 support via text message with a trained Crisis Counselor.</p>
          <a 
            href="https://www.crisistextline.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full px-4 py-2 bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Visit Website
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 ml-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-red-100 animate-on-scroll">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-4">The Trevor Project</h3>
          <div class="text-center py-4 bg-white rounded-lg mb-4">
            <p class="text-xl font-bold">866-488-7386</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">For LGBTQ+ Youth</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">The Trevor Project offers crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning youth under 25.</p>
          <a 
            href="https://www.thetrevorproject.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-full px-4 py-2 bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Visit Website
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4 ml-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-neutral-100 p-6 rounded-xl mt-12 text-center animate-on-scroll">
        <p class="font-bold text-red-700">If you are in immediate danger of harming yourself or others, please call 911 or go to your nearest emergency room.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Talk to Someone -->
  <section id="talk" class="py-16 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-4 animate-on-scroll">Talk to Someone</h2>
        <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-neutral-600 animate-on-scroll">
          Sometimes you just need someone to listen. These resources provide different ways to connect with supportive people.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <ResourceCard
          title="Teen Line"
          description="A teen-to-teen hotline and community that provides support, resources and hope to youth facing their everyday struggles."
          link="https://www.teenline.org/"
          tags={["Peer Support", "Hotline"]}
          image="https://3.files.edl.io/9ce6/24/03/26/174933-908d3b0f-10cb-4592-a907-d256b48828f6.jpg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
          external={true}
        />
        
        <ResourceCard
          title="Crisis Support Services"
          description="Local crisis support offered by trained Alameda County professionals and listeners."
          link="https://www.crisissupport.org/"
          tags={["Chat Support", "Online Therapy"]}
          image="https://www.crisissupport.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/css-logo1.png?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
          external={true}
        />
        
        <ResourceCard
          title="National Grad Crisis Line"
          description="&quot;For 25 years, three million graduate students in the U.S. have found support, counseling, and crisis-care in the face of their unique [educational] demands&quot;"
          tags={["Career", "Student debt", "Counseling", "Academic Support"]}
          image="https://images.pexels.com/photos/1181605/pexels-photo-1181605.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Finding Professional Help -->
  <InfoSection
    title="Finding Professional Help"
    description="When you're struggling with your mental health, professional support can make a big difference. Here's how to find the right help for you."
    imageSrc="https://images.pexels.com/photos/4098224/pexels-photo-4098224.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
    imageAlt="Therapist office"
  >
    <div class="space-y-4 mt-6">
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">1</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Talk to a Trusted Adult</h3>
          <p>Start by talking to a parent, guardian, school counselor, or other trusted adult about what you're experiencing. They can help you navigate the process of finding professional help.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">2</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Types of Mental Health Professionals</h3>
          <p>Different professionals provide different types of care. These include therapists, counselors, psychologists, and psychiatrists. Each has unique training and approaches to mental health care.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">3</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Finding the Right Fit</h3>
          <p>It's important to find a professional you feel comfortable with. It's okay to meet with a few different providers before deciding who to work with long-term.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">4</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">What to Expect</h3>
          <p>In your first session, the mental health professional will ask questions to understand what you're experiencing. They'll work with you to develop a treatment plan that might include regular therapy, coping strategies, and sometimes medication.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/resources/find-therapist" class="inline-block px-5 py-3 bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors shadow-md">
          How to Find a Therapist
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </InfoSection>
  
  <!-- Self-Help Resources -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-4 animate-on-scroll">Self-Help Resources</h2>
        <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg text-neutral-600 animate-on-scroll">
          While not a substitute for professional help when needed, these tools can help you manage your mental health day-to-day.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
        <ResourceCard
          title="Breathing Exercises"
          description="Simple breathing techniques to help manage anxiety and stress in the moment."
          link="/resources/breathing-techniques"
          tags={["Anxiety", "Stress"]}
          image="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3759659/pexels-photo-3759659.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
        />
        
        <ResourceCard
          title="Grounding Techniques"
          description="Practical strategies to help you stay present when overwhelmed by difficult emotions."
          link="/resources/grounding-techniques"
          tags={["Anxiety", "Panic"]}
          image="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2258536/pexels-photo-2258536.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
        />
        
        <ResourceCard
          title="Healthy Sleep Habits"
          description="Tips for improving your sleep, which can significantly impact your mental health."
          link="/resources/sleep-habits"
          tags={["Sleep", "Wellbeing"]}
          image="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3771069/pexels-photo-3771069.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
        />
        
        <ResourceCard
          title="Mood Tracking"
          description="Learn how tracking your mood can help you identify patterns and triggers."
          link="/resources/mood-tracking"
          tags={["Self-awareness", "Tool"]}
          image="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6287500/pexels-photo-6287500.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Additional Support Section -->
  <InfoSection
    title="Supporting Someone in Crisis"
    description="If you're worried about a friend or loved one who might be in crisis, here's how you can help them get the support they need."
    imageSrc="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7176301/pexels-photo-7176301.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
    imageAlt="Friends supporting each other"
    imagePosition="right"
    bgColor="bg-white"
  >
    <div class="space-y-4 mt-6">
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">1</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Take It Seriously</h3>
          <p>If someone tells you they're thinking about suicide or self-harm, always take them seriously. Listen without judgment and let them know you care.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">2</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Don't Keep It a Secret</h3>
          <p>While respecting privacy is important, safety comes first. Tell a trusted adult about your concerns, even if your friend asked you not to.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">3</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Stay With Them</h3>
          <p>If possible, don't leave someone alone if they're in crisis. Help them call a crisis line or reach out to a trusted adult.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 flex items-center justify-center mt-1">
          <span class="font-bold text-sm">4</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ml-3">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Take Care of Yourself</h3>
          <p>Supporting someone in crisis can be emotionally draining. Make sure to talk to someone about your own feelings and take care of your own mental health too.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/resources/support-friend" class="inline-block px-5 py-3 bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors shadow-md">
          Learn More About Supporting Others
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </InfoSection>
  
  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>